<subSubSection id="DDAC6573BB75E87311A74747FE9FFDB1" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="950936F8BB75E87311A74747FE9FFDB1" blockId="93.[151,1437,260,536]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87311A74747FF7AFEB4" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[151,249,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gerridae</taxonomicName>
is the second richest family of semiaquatic bugs in 
<collectingCountry id="EDA17668BB75E87312674747FC4AFEB4" box="[855,969,260,285]" name="Argentina" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, with 18 described species in 11 genera. 
<bibRefCitation id="F1274B09BB75E87311A74764FED9FEE9" author="Andersen" box="[151,346,295,320]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1982) The semiaquatic bugs (Hemiptera, Gerromorpha). Phylogeny, adaptations, biogeography and classification. Entomonograph, 3, 1 - 455." type="journal article" year="1982">Andersen (1982)</bibRefCitation>
classified the 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E873133D4764FDECFEE9" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[525,623,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gerridae</taxonomicName>
in eight subfamilies, of which 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87312DF4764FB41FEE9" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1975" box="[1007,1218,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Charmatometrinae">Charmatometrinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87315E24764FA1BFEE9" authorityName="Matsuda" authorityYear="1960" box="[1234,1432,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cylindrostethinae">Cylindrostethinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87311A7470FFF79FECC" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[151,250,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Gerrinae">Gerrinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E8731035470FFE0FFECC" authorityName="Bianchi" authorityYear="1896" box="[261,396,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Halobatinae">Halobatinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87310A7470FFDD2FECC" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1933" box="[407,593,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhagadotarsinae">Rhagadotarsinae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87313BB470FFC98FECC" baseAuthorityName="Polhemus and Polhemus" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[651,795,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trepobatinae">Trepobatinae</taxonomicName>
are represented in the Argentinean fauna. Two tribes are currently recognized in the 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87310D2472CFDC4FE21" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[482,583,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Gerrinae">Gerrinae</taxonomicName>
, following the classification proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="F1274B09BB75E873150E472CFA86FE21" author="Andersen" box="[1086,1285,367,392]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1995) Cladistics, historical biogeography, and a check list of gerrine water striders (Hemiptera, Gerridae) of the World. Steenstrupia, 21, 93 - 123." type="journal article" year="1995">Andersen (1995)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E8731426472CFAE4FE21" baseAuthorityName="Leach" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[1302,1383,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Gerrini">Gerrini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87311A747D7FEAAFE04" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1975" box="[151,297,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Tachygerrini">Tachygerrini</taxonomicName>
, both of which are present in 
<collectingCountry id="EDA17668BB75E873134F47D7FD71FE04" box="[639,754,404,429]" name="Argentina" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. The 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E873120247D7FC3AFE04" authorityName="Bianchi" authorityYear="1896" box="[818,953,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Halobatinae">Halobatinae</taxonomicName>
are classified in two tribes (
<bibRefCitation id="F1274B09BB75E87315CE47D7FE8CFE79" author="Andersen" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" refString="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Weir, T. A. (2004) Australian water bugs. Their biology and identification (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Gerromorpha &amp; Nepomorpha). Entomonograph, 14, 1 - 344." type="journal article" year="2004">Andersen and Weir 2004</bibRefCitation>
), and only the 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E873108247F4FDABFE79" authorityName="Bianchi" authorityYear="1896" box="[434,552,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halobatini">Halobatini</taxonomicName>
have been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="EDA17668BB75E873127B47F4FC3DFE79" box="[843,958,439,464]" name="Argentina" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. Four tribes are currently recognized in the 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E87311A7479FFD15FE5D" authority="(Polhemus and Polhemus 2002)" baseAuthorityName="Polhemus and Polhemus" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[151,662,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trepobatinae">
Trepobatinae (
<bibRefCitation id="F1274B09BB75E8731007479FFD0DFE5D" author="Polhemus" box="[311,654,476,501]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2002) The Trepobatinae (Gerridae) of New Guinea and surrounding regions, with a review of the world fauna. Part 6. Phylogeny, biogeography, world checklist, bibliography and final taxonomic addenda. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 33, 253 - 290. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631202 X 00154" type="journal article" year="2002">Polhemus and Polhemus 2002</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, of which only the 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E873125A479FFC6DFE5C" authorityName="J.Polhemus &amp; D.Polhemus" authorityYear="1993" box="[874,1006,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Metrobatini">Metrobatini</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB75E873157D479FFB4CFE5C" authorityName="Matsuda" authorityYear="1960" box="[1101,1231,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Trepobatini">Trepobatini</taxonomicName>
are recorded from the country.
</paragraph>
